In platform/cli/src/commands/config.ts at lines 577-581:
```
try {
  await writeAuthFile(newSecret);
} catch (err) {
  console.warn(pc.yellow(`Warning: Could not write auth.json: ${toErrorMessage(err)}`));
}
```

If writeAuthFile fails, the code continues to the server notification section (lines 583-611), where it tries to notify the server using the OLD secret. If the server responds with 200, the code prints `Secret rotated successfully.` even though the file write failed — the new secret is lost.

Fix: after the catch block, add `return;` (or `process.exit(1)`) so that a write failure aborts the command. Change the warning to an error:
```
try {
  await writeAuthFile(newSecret);
} catch (err) {
  console.error(pc.red(`Failed to write auth.json: ${toErrorMessage(err)}`));
  console.error('Secret was NOT rotated.');
  process.exit(1);
}
```
